&lt;h2 id="golden-layouthttpsgithubcomdeepstreamiogolden-layoutthe-ultimate-javascript-layout-manager">&lt;a href="https://github.com/deepstreamIO/golden-layout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">golden-layout&lt;/a>:The ultimate Javascript layout manager&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>
&lt;figure >
&lt;div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
&lt;div class="w-100" >&lt;img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/512416/4584449/e6c154a0-4ffa-11e4-81a8-a7e5f8689dc5.PNG" alt="" loading="lazy" data-zoomable />&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;/figure>
The usual import declaration does not work out of the box if we use NPM + React + Webpack because React is not a peer dependency of Golden Layout.&lt;/p>
&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>import GoldenLayout from &amp;#39;golden-layout&amp;#39;
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;p>Instead, we need to first shim the module by adding React and ReactDOM as global variable. One way to do it is to use imports loader.&lt;/p>
&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>const GoldenLayout = require(&amp;#39;imports?React=react&amp;amp;ReactDOM=react-dom!golden-layout&amp;#39;)
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre></description></item></channel></rss>